s# Pick your baseUrl here:
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3002
# @baseUrl = https://api.firecrawl.dev

### Create Browser Session (defaults)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/browser HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TEST_API_KEY}}
content-type: application/json

{}

### Create Browser Session (with options)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/browser HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TEST_API_KEY}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "ttlTotal": 600,
  "ttlWithoutActivity": 120,
  "streamWebView": false
}

### Create Browser Session (with webview streaming)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/browser HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TEST_API_KEY}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "ttlTotal": 300,
  "streamWebView": true
}

### Execute Code (Python) — replace BROWSER_ID with actual browserId
@browserId = REPLACE_WITH_BROWSER_ID

POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/browser/execute HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TEST_API_KEY}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "browserId": "{{browserId}}",
  "code": "await page.goto(\"https://docs.firecrawl.dev\")\nprint(await page.title())",
  "language": "python"
}

### Execute Code (JS) — replace BROWSER_ID with actual browserId
POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/browser/execute HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TEST_API_KEY}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "browserId": "{{browserId}}",
  "code": "await page.goto('https://example.com');\nconst title = await page.title();\nconsole.log(title);",
  "language": "js"
}

### Delete Browser Session — replace BROWSER_ID with actual browserId
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v2/browser HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv TEST_API_KEY}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "browserId": "{{browserId}}"
}

### WebSocket — webview stream (use a WS client, e.g. wscat)
# wscat -c "ws://localhost:3002/v2/browser/{{browserId}}" -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY"
